     VISN 1 logo                       What's New?

   Follow the Links to explore the most recently added content on the VISN
             1 web site. The most recent additions appear first.
     __________________________________________________________________

                         THIS MONTH - January, 2002
    Jan 10 Our Enrollment Guide has been updated with new co-payment and
                   prescription drug information for 2002.
     __________________________________________________________________

                                 PREVIOUSLY

    Dec 31 - The January issue of News at a Glance is now online. Network
    Director Post sets the record straight concerning the Network budget.

   Dec 6 - The December issue of the Network's News at a Glance newsletter
       is now online. Catch up on the latest news around the Network.

    Dec 4 - The fall issue of Veterans' Healthy Living, VISN 1's wellness
   magazine, is online. Learn about hearing loss, quitting smoking, breast
     cancer, and ways to cope in the aftermath of disaster. If you would
   like to receive this newsletter mailed to your home, let us know using
                        the Newsletter sign-up form.

   Nov 13 - The November issue of the Network newsletter News at a Glance
   has been added. Read about new staff appointments, recent legislation,
                     and other news around the Network.

    Nov 8 - The newest Community Based Outpatient Clinic in VISN 1 opened
   on Oct. 22, 2001. The Dorchester CBOC, located at 895 Blue Hill Avenue,
     Dorchester, MA, will serve veterans in the Boston neighborhoods of
                     Dorchester, Roxbury, and Mattapan.

   Nov 1 - The U.S. Government Web Portal, www.FirstGov.gov, has compiled
    a comprehensive list of helpful links related to the U.S. response to
    terrorism, including bioterrorism precautions and safe mail handling.

   Sep 27 - A Special Edition of Network 1's newsletter News at a Glance,
     "Together We Stand", was published in the wake of the September, 11
                                  tragedy.

       Sep 17 - Recently, VA New England Healthcare System leadership
      re-evaluated and revised the Network's mission, vision and values
       statement in order to better reflect our purpose in serving the
                          veterans of New England.

   Sep 17 - The Edith Nourse Rogers Memorial Veterans Hospital in Bedford,
        MA recently opened a new Community Based Outpatient Clinic in
                               Fitchburg, MA.
